Check whether or not the "g" modifier is set:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com!";
let patt1 = /Demo/g;
let res = patt1.global;
console.log(res);
Output:


Description
The global property specifies whether or not the "g" modifier is set.

This property returns true if the "g" modifier is set, otherwise it returns false.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
global	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
let a = RegExpObject.global;
Return Value
Type	Description
Boolean	Returns true if the "g" modifier is set, false otherwise
